  "is_vocab": false,
  "stimulus_html": "In planning a synthesis, it’s as important to know what not to do as to know what to do. As written, the following reaction schemes have flaws in them. What is wrong with each?",
  "questions": [
    {
      "id": 358947,
      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<img class=\"scaled-down\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBbHdWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--300fe7b89497254aee54a90e51fd310acb5f6a7d/OChem_16_10_011a.jpg\" alt=\"Benzonitrile reacts with propanoyl chloride in the presence of aluminum trichloride followed by nitric acid in the presence of sulfuric acid to form a trisubstituted benzene ring bearing a cyano, a nitro, and an acyl group.\">",
      "answers": [],
